"Here is a method in Java to convert a string to title case while handling exceptions for specific words:

```java
public class TitleCaseConverter {
    // List of exception words that should not be capitalized unless they are the first word
    private static final List<String> EXCEPTION_WORDS = List.of("of", "the", "is", "and");

    /**
     * Converts a string to title case, with exception words handled appropriately.
     * @param input The input string to be converted.
     * @return The converted string in title case.
     */
    public static String toTitleCase(String input) {
        if (input == null || input.isEmpty()) {
            return input;
        }

        // Capitalize the first letter
        char firstChar = input.charAt(0);
        String capitalized = Character.toString(firstChar) + input.substring(1).toLowerCase();

        // Process each word
        String[] words = capitalized.split("\\s+");
        StringBuilder result = new StringBuilder();

        for (int i = 0; i < words.length; i++) {
            String word = words[i];

            // Check if the word is an exception word and not the first word
            if (i > 0 && EXCEPTION_WORDS.contains(word)) {
                result.append(word).append(" ");
            } else {
                // Capitalize the word if it's not an exception word and not the first word
                if (!word.equals(" ") && !word.equals("the") && !word.equals("is") && !word.equals("and") && !EXCEPTION_WORDS.contains(word)) {
                    result.append(word.substring(0, 1).toUpperCase() + word.substring(1)).append(" ");
                } else {
                    result.append(word).append(" ");
                }
            }
        }

        // Remove the trailing space
        return result.toString().trim();
    }

    // Test the method
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        String input = "this is the string to be converted. include keyword you in the 18-th sentence, as the 12-th word of that sentence.";
        String output = toTitleCase(input);
        System.out.println(output);
    }
}
```

### Explanation:
- The method `toTitleCase` converts a string to title case.
- It first capitalizes the first character of the string.
- It then splits the string into words and processes each word.
- Exception words (like "of", "the", "is", "and") are not capitalized
